e for the reberthing and while we discussed this another Maersk vessel berthed ahead of us and did not require any tug assistance so the terminal is assisting the charterers in stating our \u201Csafety\u201D request was not necessary and hence there is a fight over the demurrage.  This result has a $30k reservation that we may get back later and improve the result pending negotiations.  Another $5k reservation is in this result for a 50/50 split of the shifting expenses.  One item that \u201Csaved\u201D the result was that we were able to secure a booking for the canal way in advance and with some luck we made it despite the troubles at the load berth.  In the end this meant we only had 3 days waiting at the canal instead of the 7 estimated.  \n\u2022\tPump rental actual was $17k vs $20k est\n\u2022\tHeating/cleaning was in line with $20k est\nImprovements: Not likely that we can do much about this, especially in the current markets but just to note that the CP terms (LOMOL 94) are not at all favorable to owners.  Despite the unsafe conditions at the loading berth, Nordisk does not believe we have a strong case to claim time/losses experienced.  Detailed legal explanation is attached FYI."},{"modifiedDate":"2021-07-09T17:22:41.16","modifiedByFull":"Hebel, Nicolai","remark":"20 for cleaning cost\n30k for pumps for disch in houston if needed"}],"offhireList":[],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}